  "text": "Numerous studies have suggested that oxidant injury to the pulmonary microvasculature is an important mechanism in the pathogenesis of ARDS [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . There are animal models to prove that pretreatment with scavengers of reactive oxygen species significantly reduces the pulmonary hypertension, hypoxia and increased microvascular permeability to proteins that otherwise characterizes ALI following infusion of endotoxin [CITATION_3] .",
